
[1]zircon

   ZIRCON, n. Called also jargon of Ceylon, a mineral originally found in
   Ceylon, in the sands of rivers, along with spinel, sapphire, tourmalin,
   and iron sand. Zircon, hyacinth, and zirconite, are regarded as
   varieties of the same species. They are essentially composed of the
   earth zirconia, with silex, and a minute portion of iron. The primitive
   form of the crystals is an octahedron, composed of two four sided
   prisms. The common form is a rectangular four sided prism.
